    <bf:originDate>1684-1699</bf:originDate>
    <bf:title>
      <bf:Title>
	<bf:mainTitle>Humphrey Morrey account book</bf:mainTitle>
      </bf:Title>
    </bf:title>
    <bf:title>
      <bf:VariantTitle>
	<bf:mainTitle>Humphrey Morrey papers</bf:mainTitle>
      </bf:VariantTitle>
    </bf:title>
    <bf:title>
      <bf:VariantTitle>
	<bf:mainTitle>Account book of a Philadelphia merchant</bf:mainTitle>
      </bf:VariantTitle>
    </bf:title>
    <bf:summary>
      <bf:Summary>
	<rdfs:label>Unsigned account book, dated between 1684 and 1699, belonging to a Philadelphia merchant, most likely Humphrey Morrey, Quaker merchant and first mayor of the city of Philadelphia, Pennsylvania. Documents goods imported and sold, the construction and repair of buildings and other structures around Philadelphia including the Chestnut Street wharf, Quaker meeting houses, and a ship; and personal and business expenses. Includes several pages of Delaware Lenape Indian words and phrases relating to trade.</rdfs:label>
      </bf:Summary>
    </bf:summary>
